# IC-Ticker-LED

Scrolling LED message ticker built at the **Interface Cultures** department of the **Kunstuniversität Linz**.  
Receives messages via MQTT and displays them on a MAX7219 LED matrix, running on a TinyPICO (ESP32).

---

## Hardware

| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| Microcontroller | [TinyPICO](https://www.tinypico.com/) (ESP32) |
| Display | MAX7219 LED matrix — 12 modules (`FC16_HW`) |
| Status LEDs | 8× WS2812 NeoPixel on GPIO 27 |
| Buttons | Red (GPIO 14), Blue (GPIO 4) |

**Wiring (TinyPICO → MAX7219):** DIN → GPIO 23 · CS → GPIO 5 · CLK → GPIO 18

---

## Getting Started

### Requirements
- [VS Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) + [PlatformIO](https://platformio.org/install/ide?install=vscode)

### First flash (USB)

1. Clone the repo and open it in VS Code — PlatformIO detects `platformio.ini` automatically.
2. In `platformio.ini`, comment out the OTA lines for the first upload:
   ```ini
   ; upload_protocol = espota
   ; upload_port = 192.168.x.x
   ```
3. Edit `src/main.cpp` — set your MQTT broker IP:
   ```cpp
   IPAddress server(xxx, xxx, xxx, xxx);
   ```
4. Connect via USB and click **Upload** (→).

### WiFi setup

On first boot the device opens a captive portal — no hardcoded credentials needed.

- Connect to AP **`IC-Ticker`** · password **`interface`**
- Open `192.168.4.1` in a browser and enter your WiFi credentials
- Credentials are saved to flash and reused on every subsequent boot

> **eduroam / WPA2 Enterprise:** The `platformio.ini` pins a specific WiFiManager commit that supports eduroam. Don't update that library without testing.

### OTA updates

After the first flash all updates go over WiFi — no USB needed.

```ini
upload_protocol = espota
upload_port = 192.168.x.x   ; device IP shown in Serial Monitor on boot
```

Click **Upload** (→) as usual.

---

## MQTT

| Topic | Payload | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `devlol/IC-Ticker` | any string (max ~95 chars) | scrolls message 5× |
| `devlol/IoTlights/color` | hex color e.g. `#FF0030` | sets NeoPixel color |

```bash
mosquitto_pub -h <broker-ip> -t "devlol/IC-Ticker" -m "Hello Interface Cultures!"
```

---

## Display behaviour

1. New MQTT message → scrolls 5×, then clears
2. Default rotation → alternates `"IC Ticker"` / `"InterfaceCultures"`
3. Every 60 s → shows current time, then date (NTP synced)
4. Deep sleep 23:00–06:00 (CET/CEST), wakes at 06:00

---

## Dependencies

| Library | Version |
|---|---|
| `majicdesigns/MD_MAX72XX` | `^3.3.0` |
| `majicdesigns/MD_Parola` | `^3.5.6` |
| `knolleary/PubSubClient` | `^2.8` |
| `FastLED/FastLED` | `^3.7.0` |
| `tzapu/WiFiManager` | pinned commit `e1f59eb` |

---

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| No portal appears | Power-cycle; or uncomment `wifiManager.resetSettings()` in `main.cpp` to force it |
| OTA fails | Check device IP in `upload_port`; device and PC must be on the same network |
| OTA fails | Check Firewall settings! |
| MQTT not working | Verify broker IP, topic names, and that port 1883 is reachable |
| Device sleeps unexpectedly | Normal — check NTP sync via Serial Monitor |
| eduroam won't connect | Only use the pinned WiFiManager commit — do not upgrade |

